2. equi, &c. Caesar rehorsed his German auxiliaries, ‘ quod minus idoneis equis utebantur ' (7. 65, 5); but speaks of the skill shown in dismounting and fighting (4. 2, 33 12. 2). The Tencteri are exceptionally noted as good horse- men Qc. 32, 2).
